    "client_msg_id": "90B79785-824F-49E5-A22C-1D87F536F6A0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The main project while I was there was a general-purpose structured editor called the Intentional Domain Workbench. You defined a schema for your language, we gave you an IDE, which you could progressively enhance with custom notations and functionality.\n_Everything_ in the system was built around tree transformations - the entire editor was a series of compiler passes from domain code to an editor language to a layout language to a graphics language - and all transformations had rich mappings between their input and output, so you could connect a pixel on the screen back to its source. \nI spent most of my time working on persistence and version control - merging of trees based on full edit history, unobtrusively modelling conflicts, etc. \nWe had a couple of pilot customers that we built workbenches for, to prove out the approach - iirc we demoed one based around administrating pensions a few times. There are screenshots for sure, not sure if there's video. ",
